This directory contains the source code
for Chapter 6. This includes

thrd-book.c - the Pthread program shown in Figure 6.9  -

thrd.c - a more interesting (but complicated) version of this program.

To compile and run these programs, enter

	gcc [thrd-book.c thrd.c] -lpthread
	./a.out

You should see a variety of program runs depending upon the type of POSIX system these are run on.
These programs were tested using gcc 3.1 on Mac OS X, Linux 2.4, and Solaris 2.8.

To run the programs illustrating Java threa priorities, compile both Java source files and enter

	java Tester

